# Check `null` before `isEmpty`

You&#39;ll just have to check for `null` before `isEmpty` each time. You could quickly create a method to help you, ie:

    private boolean isNullOrEmpty(List list) {
       return list == null || list.isEmpty();
    }
This won&#39;t cause a null pointer exception since it will not check for the 2nd condition if the first is true. ([Short-circuit evaluation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Short-circuit_evaluation))

